abstract: Corinna da Fonseca-Wollheim reviews Chamber Music Society of Lincoln Center concert, which revolved around quintet composed by Alberic Magnard, at Alice Tully Hall.
lead_paragraph: This event’s program included works by Ligiet and Poulenc in an unusually adventurous lineup for the society.

headline.main: Review: Chamber Music Society of Lincoln Center Spotlights Albéric Magnard
